    <section anchor="changes-from-rfc-7159" numbered="true" removeInRFC="false" toc="include" pn="section-appendix.a">
      <name slugifiedName="name-changes-from-rfc-7159">Changes from RFC 7159</name>
      <t indent="0" pn="section-appendix.a-1">This section lists changes between this document and the text in
RFC 7159.</t>
      <ul bare="false" empty="false" indent="3" spacing="normal" pn="section-appendix.a-2">
        <li pn="section-appendix.a-2.1"> Section 1.2 has been updated to reflect the removal of a JSON
   specification from ECMA-262, to make ECMA-404 a normative
   reference, and to explain the particular meaning of &quot;normative&quot;.</li>
      </ul>
      <ul bare="false" empty="false" indent="3" spacing="normal" pn="section-appendix.a-3">
        <li pn="section-appendix.a-3.1"> Section 1.3 has been updated to reflect errata filed against
   RFC 7159, not RFC 4627.</li>
      </ul>
      <ul bare="false" empty="false" indent="3" spacing="normal" pn="section-appendix.a-4">
        <li pn="section-appendix.a-4.1"> Section 8.1 was changed to require the use of UTF-8 when
   transmitted over a network.</li>
      </ul>
      <ul bare="false" empty="false" indent="3" spacing="normal" pn="section-appendix.a-5">
        <li pn="section-appendix.a-5.1"> Section 12 has been updated to increase the precision of the
   description of the security risk that follows from using the
   ECMAScript &quot;eval()&quot; function.</li>
      </ul>
      <ul bare="false" empty="false" indent="3" spacing="normal" pn="section-appendix.a-6">
        <li pn="section-appendix.a-6.1"> Section 14.1 has been updated to include ECMA-404 as a normative
   reference.</li>
      </ul>
      <ul bare="false" empty="false" indent="3" spacing="normal" pn="section-appendix.a-7">
        <li pn="section-appendix.a-7.1"> Section 14.2 has been updated to remove ECMA-404, update the
   version of ECMA-262, and refresh the errata list.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>
  </back>
